ConScapeRtools 0.4.22
---------
* CRAN compliance pass. `R CMD check --as-cran` returns 0 errors,
  0 warnings, 0 notes on R 4.6.0 / Windows. Fixed a test that referenced
  the vignette by its source path (`vignettes/...`) and therefore
  failed when the installed package replaced that with `doc/`; the test
  now uses `skip_if_not()` so it exercises the source when available
  and silently skips against an installed binary.
* `.Rbuildignore`: added `^vignettes/conscape_sensitivity$` (leftover
  run output), `^_tmp_.*\.R$` (temporary author scripts), and
  `^inst/examples/validate_workflows_.*\.rds$` (saved validation
  results) so they do not enter the .tar.gz.

ConScapeRtools 0.4.21
---------
* Corrected the `target_mode = "center"` workflow so it actually restricts the
  per-tile RSP absorbing target set to the tile center (previously this mode
  only changed diagnostics; the on-disk target raster matched `"full"` mode).
  Each tile now solves `Z = (I - W) \ I_target` over center-only target
  columns, which is the same per-window math that ConScape's dev
  `WindowedProblem` uses, executed against the stable bundled Julia API.
* Added `method = "sum"` to `mosaic_conscape()`. `run_conscape()` selects it
  automatically whenever `conscape_prep$target_mode == "center"`, replacing
  the legacy mean reduction whose bias was inherent to overlapping
  full-target tiles. Pass `target_mode = "full"` to `conscape_prep()` to
  recover the previous biased mean-mosaic behavior.
* Changed the default `target_mode` (under `target_mode = "auto"`) from
  `"full"` to `"center"` for all tile_d/tile_trim and centersize/buffer
  workflows. Center-target geometry is derived from the corresponding map-
  unit arguments.
* Updated `conscape_efficiency_assessment()` so `estimated_source_target_cells`
  reflects the backend's actual work per prep object: center-mode preps now
  correctly report fewer target columns of `Z`, which matches the per-tile
  ConScape problem size after the fix.
* Added `tests/testthat/test-tiled-untiled-convergence.R`, a buffer sweep
  that reports max_abs, RMSE, and layer correlation of each tile mode
  against an untiled reference. Documents when full_mean wins (small
  landscape relative to decay scale) and when center_sum wins (large
  landscape, buffer large relative to decay scale).
* Documented in `vignettes/ConScapeRtools_Guide.Rmd` and
  `vignettes/Windowed_and_Batch_Problems.Rmd` that the stable backend now
  produces the same per-window math as the dev `WindowedProblem` and is the
  recommended path for most users.
* Added `inst/examples/validate_workflows.R`, a self-contained harness that
  runs untiled, classic tiled, center-buffer, legacy full-target, and
  (optionally) dev WindowedProblem / BatchProblem on the same demo crop and
  reports max_abs, RMSE, correlation, and a relative-tolerance identity
  check against the untiled reference. The numerical output is embedded in
  the `vignettes/Windowed_and_Batch_Problems.Rmd` "Identity Validation"
  section so users can see the proof without running Julia themselves.
* The harness now also reports wall-clock timing for each workflow with
  `speedup_vs_untiled` and a `status` column, captures and reports the
  upstream error message when a dev-backend run fails, and saves the
  results to `inst/examples/validate_workflows_summary.rds` and
  `inst/examples/validate_workflows_timings.rds` for downstream auditing.
* Documented in `vignettes/Windowed_and_Batch_Problems.Rmd` "Current
  Experimental Notes" that the ConScape.jl `alg_efficiency` HEAD currently
  returns `Missing` from `ConScape.solve(..., mosaic_return = true)` in
  some configurations, breaking the dev bridge with a `MethodError` at
  `inst/extdata/conscape_dev_windowed.jl:187`. The stable backend is
  unaffected. The validation harness reports the failure with
  `status = "failed"` so it is visible in any audit run.
* `run_conscape()` now refuses sensitivity requests when the supplied
  `conscape_prep` was built with `target_mode = "center"`. Center-mode
  tiles use `target = center cells` and `source = full buffered window`,
  which violates `ConScape.sensitivity`'s `target_equal_source = TRUE`
  precondition inside every tile and makes the sum-mosaic reduction
  inappropriate for per-cell sensitivity surfaces. The error fires
  before Julia starts and points the user to the workaround
  (`target_mode = "full"`, with `landmark = 1L`). Tiled sensitivity
  even under full mode is documented as a tile-local approximation;
  untiled remains the strictly-correct path when the landscape fits.
* `run_conscape()` now dispatches the mosaic reduction PER OUTPUT LAYER
  instead of using one method for the whole run. Additive outputs
  (`fcon`, `btwn`, `btwn_qweighted`, `criticality`) use `"sum"` under
  center mode and `"mosaic"` (mean) under legacy full mode; sensitivity
  / elasticity outputs always use `"mosaic"` (mean) because they are
  tile-local landscape-summary derivatives, not pairwise sums.
  `conscape_metric_specs()` and `conscape_output_specs()` carry a new
  `mosaic_kind` field (`"additive"` vs `"averageable"`) consumed by
  `pick_mosaic_method()`. `run_diagnostics$mosaic_method` is now a
  named character vector with one entry per output layer.
* Added `tests/testthat/test-sensitivity-convergence.R`. Includes a
  pure-R unit test that confirms the center+sensitivity rejection
  fires before Julia is touched, plus a Julia-backed integration test
  (gated by `RUN_CONSCAPERTOOLS_INTEGRATION=true` and
  `RUN_CONSCAPERTOOLS_SENSITIVITY=true`) that sweeps `buffer` for
  `elasticity_quality` and `elasticity_affinity_cost_linked` against
  an untiled sensitivity reference and asserts that relative
  buffer-truncation error is non-increasing in buffer and that
  tile-local sensitivity correlates with untiled.
* Rewrote and renamed `vignettes/Windowed_and_Batch_Problems.Rmd` to
  `vignettes/Tiled_ConScape_Validation_and_Performance.Rmd`. The new
  vignette focuses on the working tiled workflow (the dev windowed /
  batch backends are currently broken upstream and have been demoted
  to a single "Experimental" section near the end). Structure: Abstract,
  Learning Goals, Workflow Map, Core Idea (with mathematical
  justification of the center-target sum-mosaic reduction), Parameters,
  Example Data, calibration via `tile_design()`, `window_design()`
  translation, a reduced demo crop, an Identity Validation section
  with TWO numerical configurations (a realistic-buffer run showing
  ~3% relative error and a wide-buffer run showing floating-point
  identity), wall-clock timing tables for both configurations,
  Decision Tree, Troubleshooting, Practical Rules, and an Experimental
  section documenting the upstream dev-backend `MethodError`.
* The vignette's worked example now uses `max_d = 1200` calibration,
  producing `tile_d = 5400 m` (20 cells) and `tile_trim = 1350 m`
  (5 cells) -- values that flow unmodified from `tile_design()` into
  every subsequent step, with no hardcoded demo overrides.

ConScapeRtools 0.4.20
---------
* Fixed Julia 1.12 `run_conscape()` logging helper dispatch for serial and threaded analyses
* Recreated `out_dir` immediately after clearing it so failed runs leave a stable output path

ConScapeRtools 0.4.19
---------
* Hardened threaded Julia `run_conscape()` execution by avoiding per-thread output redirection and treating empty-target tiles as completed outputs

ConScapeRtools 0.4.18
---------
* Reduced `tile_design()` calibration work by using a center-only synthetic target, avoiding all-target expected-cost matrices
* Clarified sensitivity workflows so prepared tiled sensitivity runs require `conscape_prep(..., landmark = 1L)`

ConScapeRtools 0.4.17
---------
* Removed an unnecessary final Julia round trip from `tile_design()` to avoid JuliaConnectoR reference-cleanup errors after successful calibration

ConScapeRtools 0.4.16
---------
* Hardened JuliaConnectoR cleanup around stale finalized references during ConScape calls
* Improved Julia-side GridRSP diagnostics for singular or degenerate graph failures
* Added regression coverage for Julia lifecycle cleanup and tiled versus untiled agreement

ConScapeRtools 0.4.15
---------
* Refactored `tile_design()` to use fully connected ideal-habitat calibration, center-cell referencing, explicit trim thresholds, and separate tile-width controls
* Made `tile_design()` calibration efficient by using one center source cell instead of an all-sources cost matrix
* Derived `tile_trim` from calibrated map-distance proximities so tiled outputs retain enough overlap to match untiled surfaces more closely
* Added tile-design diagnostics for requested and effective trim, expected tile counts, overlap area factors, and proximity at trim
* Added Julia session lifecycle helpers and `stop_julia` controls for reusing Julia across repeated ConScape workflows

ConScapeRtools 0.4.13
---------
* Added print, summary, and plot methods for core ConScapeRtools workflow objects
* Added compact summaries for ConScape result and sensitivity specification objects
* Added regression tests for the new S3 method behavior

ConScapeRtools 0.4.12
---------
* Suppressed non-actionable Julia informational logging during `tile_design()` while preserving Julia warnings and errors
* Hardened JuliaConnectoR session cleanup around stale finalized references
* Added regression tests for Julia lifecycle cleanup and logging behavior

